# Documentation Index

Use this index to load only the context relevant to the task.

| Document | Responsibility | Read when |
|---|---|---|
| [PRODUCT.md](PRODUCT.md) | Problem, users, outcomes, scope, non-goals | Clarifying product intent or scope |
| [REQUIREMENTS.md](REQUIREMENTS.md) | Testable behavior, rules, acceptance, traceability | Planning, implementing, testing, reviewing |
| [ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md) | Boundaries, module interfaces, seams, flows, dependencies, failure handling | Changing design or cross-module behavior |
| [TESTING.md](TESTING.md) | Verification commands, test layers, evidence | Implementing or reviewing any change |
| [decisions/](decisions/) | Hard-to-reverse decisions and trade-offs | Challenging an established design choice |

Conditional documents such as `CONTEXT.md`, `CONTEXT_MAP.md` with `contexts/*.md`, `DATA.md`, `API.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `OPERATIONS.md`, and `MIGRATION.md` are present only when the project needs them.

`AGENTS.md` owns durable agent rules. `PROJECT_STATE.md` owns current status. This project intentionally has no `PROCESS.md`; reusable process comes from installed skills.
